The universal property now asserts that there is a map Ud\xrightarrow {\epsilon _c} c in C, called a universal arrow from U, such that for any z\in  D, any map Uz\xrightarrow {f} x admits a unique lift to a map z\xrightarrow {g} d in D
factoring through \epsilon _x: 




