  bijection E^C(GK, F)\cong  \lbrack  E^D(G, \operatorname *{Ran}_K   F). Explicitly, this consists of a functor D\xrightarrow {\operatorname *{Ran}_K} F
  together with a natural transformation (\operatorname *{Ran}_K F) K\xrightarrow {\epsilon } F, as
